	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 9th 1:29 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am beginning to take the steps needed to get my fiery avenger, and a few things struck me as odd when I was reading through the quest...&nbsp;&nbsp;Could someone give some good roleplaying answer as to why we have to get the citizens of Neriak (dark elves) to like us in order to get our holy weapon?  I understand that this bartender is the only person who can combine this book of scale, but WHY a dark elf?  By quest's end, we are going to be able walk around neriak free of being KoS..  Does that mean I'm suppose to like dark elves now?  I like roleplaying my pally, and I think inkies are stinky.  =P  There's also a power hungry oracle who wants the book of scale...  in order to the get the lich's phylactory, we have to give the book to this oracle...  That sounds awfully selfish of a pally.  You satisfy another evil in order to further your own pally's goals...  What's the deal with that?  The part about giving the pylactory back to the lich and killing him is kewl.  That's the stuff of pally legend.  =P  Just my 2cp.  (and I'm bored at work)<br><br>Someone pls entertain my argument with a good roleplaying storylike answer.  I'd love to see some good reasons for this sort of stuff in our quests.  =)<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>44th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></tr>
