	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've been reading ahead on my quests, and have come to one conclusion:<br><br>I will not be getting my Armor of Ro or my Fiery Avenger.&nbsp;&nbsp;I quite simply don't believe that this is the way it should be done.  For no reason would any Paladin attack anything that's not evil unless they're aiding and abetting the forces of evil.  And, as far as the book is concerned, I wouldn't want any Darkling touching anything of mine.  And why would I give it to another evil creature, even if it's going to give me something to fight yet another evil creature?  This.. just isn't right.  Although I like the Fiery Defender quest.  That's okay.  It's just the Avenger that I don't like.<br><br>Dalantia<br>Knight of Passion, 16th Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonet<br>Aiyeka's Beloved Guardian, 41st Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>Kings of Brotherhood</td></tr>
